<h1><p class="post_title">About</p></h1>
<div>
<p>The Aboriginal Tourism Association of British Columbia (AtBC) is a non-profit, Stakeholder-based organization that is committed to growing and promoting a sustainable, culturally rich Aboriginal tourism industry.</p>
</div>
<p>Through training, information resources, networking opportunities and co-operative marketing programs, AtBC is a one-stop resource for First Nations entrepreneurs and communities in British Columbia who are operating or looking to start a tourism business. AtBC works closely with tourism, business, education and government organizations to help B.C.’s Aboriginal tourism businesses offer quality experiences and actively promotes these experiences to visitors and local residents.</p>
<h2>Our Vision</h2>
<p>Our Vision is a prosperous and respectful Aboriginal cultural tourism industry sharing authentic products that exceed visitor expectations.</p>
<h2>Our Mission</h2>
<p>Our Mission is to provide training, awareness, product development and marketing to support a sustainable authentic Aboriginal cultural tourism industry in British Columbia while contributing to cultural preservation and economic development.</p>
<p>To find out more about AtBC, click <a href="http://www.aboriginalbc.com/corporate/">here</a> to visit our corporate site.</p>
</div>
</div>
